review.reviewBody: We picked up Gusto while waiting on our Amtrak train to SEA. The Turkey and tuna paninis were amazing. Highly recommend!
Turkey panini is too amazing, we keep coming back for it.
there was not enough meat on the Large Pulled Pork Pizza

So far, I've tried three types of panini. I like the one with mozzarella and prosciutto the most. The mozzarella complements the saltiness of the prosciutto very well. It would be even better if the lettuce inside could be replaced with arugula as before. The tuna one is also good, but the turkey one is just okay.
The  Caprese Salad tasted spoiled and included garlic-y pesto to cover up the foul taste
